\begin_layout Section
Using the System
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Logging in
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After booting up the client, you will be presented with a login screen.
 If you have an account already, skip to 3.1.2, else go to 3.1.1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Creating an account
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once the login screen has appeared, click the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Create an account
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 button on the bottom of the form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename loginCreateAccount.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A new screen will appear, asking you for a new username and password.
 Make sure you pick a memorable password at least 5 characters long, you'll
 need it every time you log in.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once you've picked a username and password, click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Create Account
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, the system will alert you on creation success.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename CreateAccount.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Logging into an existing account
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once you have a username and password, go ahead and type them into the login
 screen, then hit submit.
 You'll be taken to the tank selection screen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename loginWithUsername.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The Tank Selection Screen
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the main screen outside of the game, it is where you will pick the
 vehicle you will fight in, as well as upgrade it and buy new tanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Selecting a tank
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Simply click the drop-down arrow on the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

select a tank
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 section and choose from the 4 default tanks, including:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The German Panzer IV, long-serving member of the panzerwaffe
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The British Crusader, famed for combat against Erwin Rommel's forces in
 north Africa
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Soviet T-34, the most recognisable tank of the war, mass produced by
 the USSR to overrun the germans
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The M4 Sherman, America's answer to the new German Panther tanks.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename selectTank.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Viewing Stats
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once you have picked a tank, its statistics will appear in a box.
 These are the values that will determine who comes out on top in the game
 and who is left a smoking pile of scrap metal, so pay attention to each
 vehicle's strengths and weaknesses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can scroll through the stats with the bar on the right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename viewStats.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Upgrading your tanks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you have accumulated some experience (XP), you can use it to make your
 war machine even more potent.
 Open the upgrade screen by clicking 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Upgrade tank
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 from the selection screen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename upgradeClick.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You can now pick which stat to upgrade.
 Choose carefully, because there is a maximum amount you can upgrade any
 vehicle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Upgrade your selected stat by clicking the button next to the value.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename doUpgrade.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once you are happy with your new, bigger, badder war machine, click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Confirm
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and the changes will be sent and applied.
 Congratulations, you are now even more powerful!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Upgrade.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Purchasing a new Tank
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Have you been in the same tank for a while? Looking for some new armour?
 It may be time to look into getting a new tank.
 Be warned, these upgraded beasts aren't cheap, but they are exceptionally
 powerful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Start by clicking 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Buy a tank
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 from the selection screen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename buyTank.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A new screen will open, and you can scroll through the list of available
 tanks.
 Select one which looks good and the amount of XP needed will show.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename buyTank2.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once you're happy, click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Buy!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and the tank will be delivered to your garage immediately.
 Try it out and see just how powerful your new armour is!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Entering a Game
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Finding a Server
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Joining a game is as easy as getting 2-8 people together, the server owner
 will tell you their IP address and the server's port, you can type this
 into the selection screen, hit 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Roll Out!
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and you will be connected to the server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Refer to the Server Manual for a tutorial on how to host your own server.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename enterAddress.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Make sure the Address is in the form [ip] : [port]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename rollOut.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

